Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4). Dice @tomato{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lime{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine minced onion, tomato, half the cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @vegan chipotle mayonnaise{4%tablespoon} with a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, until lightly browned, ~{3-5%minutes} (it will cook through in Step 5). Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips. Drain and rinse @black beans{1}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add green pepper, sliced onion, and half the @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step). Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly charred and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Transfer to a plate. Reserve pan.

Use pan used for chicken here.

Heat same pan over medium-high heat. Add beans, @Tex-Mex paste{1%tablespoon}, remaining Southwest Spice Blend, and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has mostly evaporated, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from heat; gently mash beans with a #potato masher{} or back of a #spoon{}. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Drizzle @flour tortillas{6} with @olive oil{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings); brush or rub to coat all over. Arrange on a #baking sheet{} in a single layer (divide between 2 sheets for 4). Gently prick each tortilla in a few places with a #fork{}.

Bake on top rack, flipping halfway through, until lightly golden, ~{4-5%minutes} per side. (For 4, bake on top and middle racks; flipping tortillas and swapping rack positions halfway through.) > Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Once tortillas are toasted, remove sheet from oven. Carefully spread each tortilla with smashed beans, then top with veggies and @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}.

Return to top rack until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add chicken to tostadas along with veggies, then top with Mexican cheese blend. Return to top rack until chicken is cooked through and cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide tostadas between plates. Top with pico de gallo, vegan chipotle lime sauce, and remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.